        'Isolation', 'Dynamic Stretching', 'Beginner', 'None', 'The rocking soleus emphasis ankle mobilization exercise is a form of dynamic stretching used to warm up the muscles of the calves.
Warming up the calves and improving ankle mobility is important for nearly every leg exercise, as well as alleviating calf muscle tightness which can lead to postural imbalances.', 'Set up with your foot on a slanted surface with your knee bent.
Rock your knee forward while keeping your heel down and torso in a neutral position.
Move the knee forward until you feel a significant stretch in the calf.
Then, rock back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.', 'Watch for a variety of compensations which typically present when someone has excessive tone within the posterior aspect of the calf:
The arch collapses
The leg internally rotates (observe the kneecap or simply palpate the tib/fib complex as you complete repetitions)
The heels rises off the floor
The hips will rotate as they respond to rotation from the lower leg
